  "authoritative_product_boundary": "Cagrilintide remains an investigational long-acting amylin analogue. REDEFINE 1 included a cagrilintide monotherapy arm and continues an extension through 2026. The United States regulatory application filed in December 2025 concerns the fixed combination CagriSema, not catalogue CGL vials or cagrilintide monotherapy.",
  "human_evidence_boundary": "A 706-participant phase 2 dose-finding trial established cagrilintide monotherapy weight-management evidence. REDEFINE 1 subsequently included cagrilintide 2.4 mg as an active monotherapy arm alongside CagriSema, semaglutide and placebo. Separate monotherapy phase 3 RENEW studies were initiated.",
  "safety_source_boundary": "The dominant reported adverse events are gastrointestinal disorders and administration-site reactions. Amylin-related gastric, nutritional and interaction effects remain formulation- and dose-specific. CagriSema safety and submission status cannot be transferred to unverified cagrilintide powder.",
